Project Case Study Wireframe (AECS)

Case Study Structure:

[1. Project Hero]
- Project name
- Location
- System type
- Engineering scale

[2. Problem Definition]
- Architectural challenge
- Structural constraints
- Design requirements

[3. Engineering Challenge]
- Load / span / geometry issues
- System selection reasoning

[4. System Solution]
- Selected ceiling system
- Engineering logic
- Material strategy

[5. Execution Flow]
- Installation stages
- Site constraints
- Engineering control points

[6. Result Section]
- Final outcome
- Visual documentation

[7. Engineering Breakdown]
- Technical diagrams
- System validation
- QA/QC notes

[8. CTA]
- Request similar engineering system
